    <example id="exam-00002" xmlns="http://cnx.rice.edu/cnxml">
    <title>Ordering the Magnitude of Units</title>
    <exercise id="exer-00003">
    <problem id="prob-00003">
    <para id="para-00013">Order the measures from smallest unit to largest unit.</para>
    <para id="para-00021">centimeter, millimeter, decimeter</para>
    </problem>
    <solution id="sol-00002">
    <para id="para-00014">Looking at the metric prefixes, we can see that the prefix order from smallest unit to largest unit is milli-, centi-, deci-, so the order of the units from smallest to largest is millimeter, centimeter, decimeter.</para>
    </solution>
    </exercise>
    </example>
